CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 29, 1967, pg. 3, reads: "'Double Parking' Problem Again - That most common problem which keeps popping up for motorists on Hill District thoroughfares was snapped again in action by the Courier photographer in above photo taken in the vicinity of Herron and Wylie Ave. Here, a motorist stops in the middle of the street, on the wrong side and block traffic coming in the opposite direction while he unloads a few packages."
TitMainTitle: Car with opened trunk, double parked on wrong side of street, on Wylie Avenue with storefronts, including one with King Edward Cigars sign in window, Hill District
